<TITLE> Hasina sad at no contact with children on birthday: Lawyer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 28 (bndews24.com)  Sheikh Hasina is optimistic that she will soon be released, though she was sad at not being able to talk with her children on her birthday Friday. "Sheikh Hasina believes she will soon be able to leave jail," the detained former prime minister's relative and lawyer barrister Fazle Noor Tapash said to reporters after visiting her in the special jail on Sangsad Bhaban complex. "She was sad as she could not talk with her son and daughter on her birthday. However, she is well. She has asked for blessings from the people," he added. Tapash also said Hasina had asked party leaders and workers to remain united. "She has asked all to remain patient." Hasina's cousin and protocol officer Monjila Farukh told reporters: "Sheikh Hasina hopes that she will get justice if the trial is fair." "She has no allegation against anybody. She is well and has asked the people to pray for her," Monjila said after she met the Awmi League chief in the afternoon. A number of relatives were allowed to visit her Friday, including grand-daughters Namira, 7, and Arial, 8. bdnews24.
